DESCRIPTION:Join us on Wednesday\, April 29\, from 4 - 7 PM at Whispering Vine - South Creek for a tasting featuring Caymus.\nTasting Fee: $35 per person (Buy a tasting bottle and the tasting fee is refunded.)\nFeatured Wines:\n- Caymus-Suisun Grand Durif 2021 – $44.99 – This Suisun Valley Durif shows dense dark fruit\, cracked pepper\, and a savory edge that keeps the wine lifted instead of heavy.\n- Round Pond Kith & Kin Cabernet Sauvignon 2022 – undefined undefined\, undefined undefined – The nose opens with bright red cherry\, cranberry\, and a touch of allspice.\n- Leviathan Red Wine 2022 – undefined undefined – This red blend is dark\, polished\, and broad on the palate\, bringing together black cherry\, cassis\, plum\, and baking spice with a streak of freshness underneath.\n- The Calling Russian River Pinot Noir 2023 – undefined undefined – Bing cherry\, wild strawberry\, red plum\, and a little clove and nutmeg lead the nose.\n- Hartford Court Russian River Chardonnay 2024 – $26.99 – This Chardonnay opens with citrus\, crisp green apple\, nectarine\, and a little tropical lift.\nCome explore Caymus Wines and find your favorite bottle. Buy a bottle from the tasting and your fee is refunded.
LOCATION:85 Foothill Rd Ste 1 Reno\, NV 89511
SUMMARY:Caymus Tasting
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR